    • Constructor Detail

      • AudioHeader

        public AudioHeader()
        An empty constructor. Mainly to be used when you read data from a file and you want to set the values of the AudioHeader object one by one.

      • AudioHeader

        public AudioHeader(String format,
                   int numberOfChannels,
                   int sampleRate,
                   int byteRate,
                   int blockAlign,
                   int bitsPerSample,
                   int dataLengthInBytes)
        Constructs a new AudioHeader object from the parameters. Mainly to be used when you're about to write audio data to a file and want to set all the parameters simultaneously.
        Parameters:
        format - the audio format as a String (e.g. "WAVE")
        numberOfChannels - the number of audio channels
        sampleRate - the number of audio samples per second
        byteRate - the number of bytes per second (sample rate * (bits per sample / 8) * number of channels)
        blockAlign - the number of bytes per one sample for all channels (number of channels * (bits per sample / 8))
        bitsPerSample - the amount of bits used to save one audio sample
        dataLengthInBytes - the total amount of audio data
